title: ICE in NLL diagnostics

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(nll)] use std::cell::Cell; fn check<'a, 'b>(x: Cell<&'a ()>, y: Cell<&'b ()>) where 'a: 'b, { } fn test<'a, 'b>(x: Cell<&'a ()>, y: Cell<&'b ()>) { let f = check; f(x, y); } fn main() {} ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.61.0-dev binary: rustc commit-hash: unknown commit-date: unknown host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.61.0-dev LLVM version: 14.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` ```
